{
  "texts": [
    "[13] investigated the performance of adapter models on long legal documents.",
    "Consistently with previous works, the authors found that bottleneck adapters outperform FFT, and provide better zero-shot cross-lingual capability.",
    "Their findings are based on the MultiEURLEX dataset, which consists of 65,000 EU law texts in 23 languages, categorised at multiple levels of detail (between 21 and 567 categories).",
    "In some aspects, this dataset is comparable to the dataset for sub-task 3 that we explore in this work, as both datasets are multilabel and multilingual, and have a comparable number of labels at MultiEURLEX's lowest level.",
    "However the style of EU law is naturally much more rigid and very different to news articles."
  ]
}